@synchro-dentally1965 I have no doubt as an experienced scientist and experimenter, Robert is fully aware of the issues. My concern is for the inexperienced or ill-informed who only has access to a plasma cutter or oxy-acetylene torch, watches the angle-grinder cutting and doesn't see the preparation process for safe cutting. 
The UK has gone a long way to raise safety awareness in the general populace, but that doesn't hold for all international viewers.
I love this channel for its "can do" approach, particularly the lessons we learn when things don't work quite as we hoped. "Don't try this at home, kids" without giving reasons is simply not the channels approach - we are encouraging exploration.
